	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good info, but a few minor things.<br><br>A tick is 6 seconds, not 4<br><br>and<br><br>If you have to fight multiple enemies, make sure your pet is damage shielded, the aggro from the damage shield is counted against the pet.<br><br>Also, if you have multiple mobs on your pet, make sure to /assist your pet rather then assuming he is on the mob you commaded him to attack. He more the likely won't be. You should re-assist every time you nuke just to be safe unless a single cast will finish it.<br><br>Of course, a couple of casts should be enough to do it when added to pet damage... fast hitting, low HP mobs like bloodgill goblins are the easiest to take several of at once.<br><br>Because of the mages lack of crowd control you may be better off just zoning though, if you have two or more mobs, unless you pulled multiples deliberately of course.<br>&nbsp;<br>Kranken<br>Arch Convoker<br>&lt;Old Continent&gt;, Xev</td></tr>
