	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 12th 12:51 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.30]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Couple of things that are just sort of common sense.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>1) Definitely only nuke the mob your pet is attacking.  Even if one is beating on your back, ignore it and bomb the one pet is on.  <br><br>2) Air pet rules in this situation.  If you get in a situation where you are very likely to get unwanted adds (like hunting in Stonebrunt Mtns.) the air pet, with its stun ability, will give you the time to let your pet aggro the second mob.  <br><br>3) My personal most important rule of playing EQ:  If things start to look screwy, zone.  When the first unexpected thing happens in your battle, whether it is an unexpected add, a couple of fizzles in a row, or simply a tougher mob than expected, zone Then, don't wait. <br><br>4) Try to stay away from the multiple enemies situation from the very start.  Multiple enemies, at best, equals you get hit.  You get hit,  means you are going to have to sit on your rump to heal.  And that is what slows down the exp gain.  You can get back mana quicker than hit points, and multiple mobs, in the best of situations, are going to cost you some hitpoints.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
