	   <tr><td colspan=2>The point I'm driving at is that it depends, not entirely on your equip, but on your play style. If you know how to pet kite and chain summon, a mage can solo damn near anything. I've heard rumors of epic mages soloing naggy by chain summoning. Show me a bard that can do that.<br><br>Now I'm not claiming that we're the best soloers either, Necros have us beat in a couple areas, but we have a few things over on them too. They can fear and dot, but we have em beat nuke wise. With the braclet and ring foci any mage over 44 can do around 700 damage in a 5.2 second cast. With channeling, good ac and a bit of luck, you can nuke a creature down to nothing without ever needing a pet. Zheart optional. Actually, with the phantom armor and shielding lines we get our own killer ac buffs and inherent hp regen. And around 40 pretty much any mage can outsolo pretty much any group of the same level. And this was before focus items. Read the boards on magecompendium if you want stories to that effect.<br><br>If ya wanna solo as a mage you gotta know how to play your class. That means going in and taking hits for your pet occasionally, pet kiting, and chain summoning. If you know how to do these THEN you can be an extremely effective soloer.<br><br>And yer forgetting AFK exp too. Show me a necro that can summon a pet and walk away for a half a day while it rips the hell out of a spawn. (talking of the epic here).<br><br>Part of it is equip, yes, but the rest of it is knowing the advantages and limitations of your class. And no, mages aren't the best soloers, but we're up there. Particularly with all the new stuff we've gotten lately.<br><br>There are classes that can do things we can't, but we can do things that other classes can't. It's called class balance. You can't point to any class and say that they're flat out the &quot;best&quot; soloer. I've done things that I know a necro woulda had a damn hard time with, and vice versa. It's all situational.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<br><br>PS: never mentioned NToV. I'm sayin I have some of the best BUYABLE equip, and buyable tends to lean toward the metiocre at higher levels. Ya curious about what I have check my profile.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
