	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm not trying to start a flame war, but what you're saying simply doesn't make any sense, period.<br><br>&quot;The point I'm driving at is that it depends, not entirely on your equip, but on your play style. If you know how to pet kite and chain summon, a mage can solo damn near anything. I've heard rumors of epic mages soloing naggy by chain summoning. Show me a bard that can do that.&quot;<br><br>How about a bard that can do better? Stronghorn ring a bell? How about Klandicar? And whatever you've heard about 52 mages with epics soloing naggy, they're just that. Rumors. You can try to chain him but he'll summon you the instant you dismiss your pet.<br><br>&quot;ow I'm not claiming that we're the best soloers either, Necros have us beat in a couple areas, but we have a few things over on them too. They can fear and dot, but we have em beat nuke wise. With the braclet and ring foci any mage over 44 can do around 700 damage in a 5.2 second cast. With channeling, good ac and a bit of luck, you can nuke a creature down to nothing without ever needing a pet. Zheart optional. Actually, with the phantom armor and shielding lines we get our own killer ac buffs and inherent hp regen. And around 40 pretty much any mage can outsolo pretty much any group of the same level. And this was before focus items. Read the boards on magecompendium if you want stories to that effect.&quot;<br><br>I read the magecompendium boards, actually. But regardless, yes, I have done the outsolo groups thing on occasion, when I was level 40. But regardless, what I am trying to say is, this game is not about soloing. Except in very specific circumstances, grouping is <i>always</i> better then soloing, especially so once you get to 55ish and dark blue mobs can give you a serious run for your money on occasion. Now, yes mages have one thing over necromancers. We do our damage <i>fast.</i> However, because of a general lack of mana regen this ability is more useful in a group situation where you more then liekly have good melee and possibly KEI. With how poorly pets taunt chain nuking when soloing is suicide as a general rule. (except in quick fights with an epic anyway, and how many mages even <i>have</i> that blasted thing)<br><br>&quot;If ya wanna solo as a mage you gotta know how to play your class. That means going in and taking hits for your pet occasionally, pet kiting, and chain summoning. If you know how to do these THEN you can be an extremely effective soloer.&quot;<br><br>You're talking to a mage who solo'd high blues at 55. I know these things:D<br><br>&quot;And yer forgetting AFK exp too. Show me a necro that can summon a pet and walk away for a half a day while it rips the hell out of a spawn. (talking of the epic here).&quot;<br><br>Yeah, if you wanna risk getting suspended for it.<br><br>&quot;There are classes that can do things we can't, but we can do things that other classes can't. It's called class balance. You can't point to any class and say that they're flat out the &quot;best&quot; soloer. I've done things that I know a necro woulda had a damn hard time with, and vice versa. It's all situational.&quot;<br><br>I invite you to name a mob that you can solo and an equivelently equipped/skilled necromancer can't. Or heck, even a monk who has decent stuff. And yes, it's all situational. <br><br>Now, I'm not trying to flame anyone. I'm <i>not</i> trying to say that mages suck at soloing. If done properly, mages can be pretty good. But what I <i>am</i> trying to say is that, unless you're a necromancer, shaman, or melee with NToV/Luclin boss equipment soloing is inefficient and pointless past a certain level, and really it makes no sense to say a class is or isn't good solely based on what they can or can't solo in a game that wasn't designed with soloing in mind in the first place.<br><br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun May 12 10:49:24 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Kranken<br>Arch Convoker<br>&lt;Old Continent&gt;, Xev</td></tr>
