<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=101781791957069></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101781791957069><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101781791957069>RE: Pets n Weapons</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101781791957069#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73372><span id=Sage>Malaclypse</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>142 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 3rd 2:16 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, yes and no. According to <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com" target=_new>http://eq.castersrealm.com</a> it does. The damage cap (max damage on a hit) on your pets is decided by the level of the pet, which is randomly determined. Like 1 to 3 levels below your toon's current level I think.<br><br>The exact damage statistics on pets are on <a href="http://www.magecompendium.com" target=_new>http://www.magecompendium.com</a><br><br>Now personally I haven't noticed that much difference between a pet with weapons and a pet without, however it's still worth summoning them.<br><br>At lvl 20 your pets get dual wield, but only if you give them two weapons. Later in the game (lvl 40 I *think*) they get dual wield without.<br><br>Dual wield doesn't increase the actual damage your pet does each hit, but it allows them to randomly do an extra hit with their off hand weapon.<br><br>Even when your pets dual without weapons it's still worth summoning them, because at that point in the game you get summoned weapons with stats on em. Dagger of symbols for instance, adds 10 to disease, magic and poision resists if ya give your pet two of em. Also, swords of runes have a 50 dd proc against summoned creatures.<br><br>Any weapons you give your pets will act as if they were on a player character. Stat additions, procs.. they all work. Not exactly sure how ratio effects the pet, castersrealm is a bit cryptic on that point.<br><br>Armor works the same way. Ya wanna give your pet a full suit of cobalt, then it will equip and use it. Bit of a drastic example, but you get the idea.<br><br>So, in short (too late) summon everything you can for your pet. Armor, coldstones, rings of flight, shards of the core... the works. Anything with AC or stats. You can boost your pets AC by about 100 points like that. The difference between a nekked lvl 40 fighter and one with armor.<br><br>And granted, it's a royal bitch equipping a pet up each time you summon it, but trust me. It WILL save your arse.<br><br>That and a pet with weapons looks really NEAT.<br><br>AND you can give it no drop equip ya can't use.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, The extremly well dressed Mad Mage of Povar.<br><br>FEAR MY PANTS! BEWARE THE SQUIRREL EMPIRE!<br><br><br>PS: Ya want a real neat question, figure out if the summoned foci work with pets. hehe.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Apr&nbsp;&nbsp;3 02:14:23 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
