	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101697778799902><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101697778799902>RE: newbie in need of help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101697778799902#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=95490><span id=Sage>Sir Zonkz</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>44 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 24th 8:53 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.85]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dashera, what server are you playing on? Because of the differances in server economies, it's hard to give a really detailed answer to your question without knowing. I tend to play on Seventh Hammer and Fironia Vie~ There are some major price diferances because of the server age. Because almost nothing on FV is NODROP, there are a ton of things that are cheeper~ quest items especially, and some things you can buy on FV (like the Eye of Trust) that you just can't purchase on any other server. Many items on FV are more expensive than other servers because the Trivial Loot Code (TLC) is in effect EVERYWHERE. Because of the TLC, high level characters can't just farm items for sale. Anyways~ here is a general list of items and prices, but remember that this isn't server specific (but mostly by prices I've seen on 7th Hammer and E'ci), and I left off any NODROP items for sale on FV:<br><br>Pri&nbsp;&nbsp;: Black Tome w/ Silver Runes ~ 200pp<br>Sec  : Stein of Muggok ~ 150pp<br>Ear  : Golden Ear Stud ~ 20pp ea<br>Neck : Golden Star Amulet ~ 25pp<br>Face : Twilight Cloth Veil ~ 100pp<br>Head : Elemental Binder ~ 100pp<br>Ring : Ring of Frost ~ 50pp<br>Ring : Obsidian Ring of Quintessence ~ 40pp<br>Wrist: Golden Jaded Bracelet ~ 30pp ea<br>Chest: Robe of the Oracle ~ 250pp<br>Legs : White Scaled Leggings ~ 100pp<br>Waist: Black Lace Sash ~ 100pp<br>Feet : Polished Bone Hoop~ 150pp<br><br>Instead of buying Raw Silk armor for the rest of the slots~ I would buy a large sewing kit. You are going to kill sooo many spiderlings/spiders in your first few levels that you can just make it yourself. Raw silk trivs at 36, so it shouldn't be hard to do, and you are rasing a skill you'll want later.<br><br>Some people might argue Bracelet of Woven Grass over the Golden Jaded Bracelets, but in the lower levels the ac/hp/mana will be more benificial, and cost less. <br><br>You should also get your baking up (it's pretty easy to get baking up to 135 in an hour or so, especially once you have all your INT gear on) and make yourself some Blackened Tier'Dal (+1 Dex, +2 Int, +1 Agi - triv at 62) or Gnome Kabobs (+2 Dex, +2 Int - triv at 56). Being a Magician it is easy to make stat foods last forever.<br><br>Hope this helps~<br>&nbsp;<br>~ Zonkz ~<br></td></tr>
