	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pickerd, don't be aggressive toward someone who express his VALID opinion in a respectful way =P<br><br>Your points have some flaws in them, you are not seeing the big picture.<br><br><br>&gt;1. Give chain-casting of pets another look. If we could start summoning a pet when our current one has say, less than 10% health left. And the new summon would suicide the other pet and the new one (yes unbuffed) would take its place. Thus we would have to have the pet immediatly go back into battle and we face the choice of it going unbuffed or using that time/mana for nuking <br><br>Well I don't really get your point. Chain casting works like that already, you CAN summon new pet while old one is still up, just need to kill him with /pet get lost just before you finish casting new pet. I used that a lot in the old days to solo dino in oot at 50. =)<br><br>&gt;2. Give us some form of escape other than gate. Its not that much to ask. The &quot;If your pet dies, you die&quot; thing is really lame. Whether it be a snare like thing or movement enhancement. If you continue to insist that the &quot;root&quot; lie in the pet. At least make it work better. It shouldnt be hard to put into logical effect given that mages are supposed to be master's of elements to some degree whether summoning beings of, or elements themselves. <br><br>Well get jboots or traveler's boots... Gate works pretty well when you don't wait till it's too late to cast. And pet root works very well if you malise the target. Mages have survived for 3 years without root, we still can. I would like to have shadowstep, but that would be a bonus.<br><br>&gt;3. Increase the duration of our DS, even at the expense of more mana cost. I've stated above why. Or, for damage shields or any buff for that matter, the caster of said buff should get a message when it wears off of anyone. We get one when it wears off our pets why not others? Sure the buff heavy classes would get spammed by their buffs dropping but tough. If they dont like it, they can filter it (Providing if it were put in, there was enough intelligence to make it filterable) <br><br>2 solutions, sheild yourself or your pet too, so you know when it fades, or learn to time your buffs. Every other buffing class work like that, why should mages be different. As for duration, our sheilds are by far the most efficient way of dealing damage for a mage (except pets), making them last longer... /shrug, they are already better dmg/mana ratio than DD...<br><br>&gt;4. Take our weapons/items/whatever it is that we can summon and give them a scale, that is proportional to our level. That is, I summon a dagger at level 1, I get a normal dagger with normal stats, but I summon said dagger at 60, I might be looking at something alot stronger, perhaps with a proc. Also with summon arrows, 3damage 50range (maybe its 75) gets old. Perhaps having damage and range go up per so many levels? (Though not as much as fletching could produce to placate the Fletching zealots out there). <br><br>Actualy with luclin now out, our summons overall are really nice, the arrows are great considering how little mana it takes to summon 60 of them... dagger of symbols are better than lvl 1 daggers, we now can summon armor and resist items, our summons are WAY more useful than they used to be.<br><br>&gt;5. Our self only phantom armor's are an awesome line of spell. If they could be cast on group/others that would give us something nice to cast on others. As it sits Mages are SELF SELF SELF SELF SELF,as far as buffs go. (Unless you count pet buffs but those are 4 (5) buffs spread out between 60 levels) but its repeatedly stated they aren't necessarily a solo class. <br><br>Mages are not a buff class, period. There's no reason phantom line should be casteable on others, it's a nice bonus for US only, learn to like it like that. Our role in a group is not to buff, it's to deal insane damage, and we are good at that.<br><br>&gt;6. Give us SOME kind of mana regen. My suggestion is that as an alternative to Burnout on a pet. We can cast some sort of Elemental Bond spell on the pet. Explanation being that the creature being tied to whatever Plane it came from can channel extra magical energy to us through there. Of course that makes our pets less effective in combat. But thats where the balance comes in. <br><br>Do some research, mages have 2 type of mana regen now. Transon's phantasmal protection (new upgrade to phantom armor line in luclin) has a 3 point mana regen built in, wich stacks with clarity line. And mod rods V.2 are INSANE, especialy if you can get high end luclin items with right click rune (orb of lost souls or sheild of auras come to mind, there`s prolly others out there too)<br><br>If you think beastlords are so much superior to us, give up mage and go make one hehe. Class envy rarely leads to anything constructive.<br><br>Woonnusseek Brainstorm &lt;The Dark Exile&gt; <br>7th Hammer server <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721</a><br><br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
