	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 10th 6:40 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I have been in SK for over a month now and I just got my cloak about 30min ago and I have some information and ideas that can help you find this stupid winged beast. Ok, first of I noticed that it does not have a set spawn point (contrary to what some people think). But, she seems to spawn in the area between the bird house and paw. And from what I observed, she never went north of paw. I also have one little thing that can kind of give us Mages a leg up (a friend told me about this). What you do is find a spot between the bird house and paw (that way you'll hopefully be somewhat near it when it spawns) and make a hotbutton. Have the first line be&nbsp;&nbsp;/pet attack Quillmane   and have the next line be  /assist &lt;insert pet name here&gt;     Now, if Quill is up your pet will attempt to attack it, and odds are that it will be to far a way to do so. So if you do get it on you Mage &quot;ghetto&quot; track, you then run around and keep telling you pet to attack, and make sure you have taunt on because if you get anywhere near Quill it will come charging at you. Now this is not a sure fire way to find Quill, but it gives us a much bigger chance of getting to Quill before a druid/ranger does. And without this little trick I would of never found the stupid thing.<br>&nbsp;<br>Filadan Miraz,<br>High Elf Magician,<br>Master of the Orb,<br>Keeper of the Art,<br>Quellious Server</td></tr>
